We do in-house training, for which I usually teach JUnit and Ant.  I don't
think this applies to what you are asking, but I wouldn't mind getting a
peek at the objectives you've created.
 
-Jason

-----Original Message-----
From: STEPHEN CRANS [mailto:stephen-n-crans@...]
Sent: Saturday, September 01, 2001 10:55 PM
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [junit] Request for Training Resources Information


I am looking for others who are teaching classes on the use of JUnit, Ant
and Cactus.  I would appreciated any information you can provide me on
organizations or individuals giving instructor lead training on these
technologies (or interested in doing so).  I have identified a lot of
learning objectives to pass on in this training.  I would like very much to
have more advanced courses to pass my students on to when I have taught them
what I know.  Frequently, the students also want on site consulting, so
please tell me what you have to offer in that category, should it apply.
